body_html:
Well, this issue is not related with the repo itself ATM. I am the issuer of the ticket that have been mentioned.

I have opened the ticket as soon as I got the error. First, they have closed it saying that it was a duplicate, it was not. Then they have reopened it but set it to "Low" priority, yeah a system breaking bug is not important as it seems. Now, the repo maintainer haven't fixed the issue for days.

I have also made a pull request here, fixing the problem but I'm waiting for it to get a review. Even after they accept it, binaries of the new version might not be here for weeks.

This issue probably will be closed due to its unrelated-ness but you can go and change the occurrences of "tensorflow.contrib.tensorboard" with the new separate tensorflow, you are all good for now.

body:
Well, this issue is not related with the repo itself ATM. I am the issuer of the ticket that have been mentioned.

I have opened the ticket as soon as I got the error. First, they have closed it saying that it was a duplicate, it was not. Then they have reopened it but set it to "Low" priority, yeah a system breaking bug is not important as it seems. Now, the repo maintainer haven't fixed the issue for days.

I have also made a pull request here, fixing the problem but I'm waiting for it to get a review. Even after they accept it, binaries of the new version might not be here for weeks.

This issue probably will be closed due to its unrelated-ness but you can go and change the occurrences of "tensorflow.contrib.tensorboard" with the new separate tensorflow, you are all good for now.
